{"parse":{"title":"War referendum","pageid":10399301,"revid":841606582,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>War referendum</b> is a proposed type of <a href=\"/wiki/Referendum\" title=\"Referendum\">referendum</a> in which citizens decide whether a nation should go to war. No such referendum has taken place.\n</p><p>The earliest idea of a war referendum came from <a href=\"/wiki/Marquis_de_Condorcet\" title=\"Marquis de Condorcet\">Marquis de Condorcet</a> in 1793 and <a href=\"/wiki/Immanuel_Kant\" title=\"Immanuel Kant\">Immanuel Kant</a> in 1795.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ballot_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ballot-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=War_referendum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Ludlow_Amendment\" title=\"Ludlow Amendment\">Ludlow Amendment</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=War_referendum&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-ballot-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-ballot_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Bolt, Jr., Ernest C. (1977). <i>Ballots Before Bullets, The War Referendum Approach to Peace in America 1914-1941</i>. Charlottesville: University Press of Virginia. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0813906628\" title=\"Special:Book